medical or medical research purposes.
(d) If under section 6(e) section 6 of this chapter the coroner
requires an autopsy to be performed upon a decedent, the coroner may
authorize the removal of one (1) or both of the decedent's corneas for
donation to an eye bank for transplantation, if the following conditions
exist:
(1) The decedent's corneas are not necessary for successful
completion of the autopsy.
